cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.OH, cs.RO, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a cellular network for underwater wireless optical communications, which involves designing a network architecture, addressing design challenges, and discussing potential applications. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper employs optical orthogonal codes (OOC) as signature codes for underwater mobile users. Information theory deals with the study of communication systems and their limits, which includes coding theory and channel coding. 

3. cs.OH (Other Computer Science) - The paper discusses underwater localization and positioning schemes based on the proposed cellular network. This topic may fall under the scope of other computer science sub-categories. 

4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper mentions the use of the proposed network as infrastructure for underwater sensor networks for real-time monitoring. Robotics deals with the design, construction, and operation of robots, which may include underwater robots for monitoring purposes. 

5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may involve software engineering aspects such as designing and implementing the network architecture, developing algorithms for power control and blockage avoidance, and addressing scalability issues.
